                            <comment id="17701915" author="chrisegerton" created="Fri, 17 Mar 2023 17:28:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=imcdo&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;imcdo&quot;&gt;imcdo&lt;/a&gt; for filing this. I believe the root cause is slightly different than what you initially described on the ticket, so I&apos;ve updated the description with something more plausible given the changes in the PR where this was originally discussed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is definitely worth addressing as it is a regression in behavior and can cause clusters to fail after upgrades. Hopefully people aren&apos;t leaving invalid SSL properties in their worker configs when using HTTP for their REST API, but there&apos;s no reason that their cluster should break if they are.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll file a PR to fix this sometime today.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;CC &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=gharris1727&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;gharris1727&quot;&gt;gharris1727&lt;/a&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
